The paper proposes a human-centered approach using visual analytics techniques to evaluate the quality of time series data generated by Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs). This suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of GANs for generating data also suggests computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) as potential sub-categories. Finally, the use of visual analytics techniques implies a focus on visualization and human-centered approaches, which could fall under social and information sciences (cs.SI).
